findings.poc:
1. Create a DH object using a method that does NOT set DH_FLAG_CACHE_MONT_P (e.g., a custom DH_METHOD or certain engine-backed methods).
2. Perform DH key exchange with a victim.
3. Measure the time taken for DH_compute_key / ossl_dh_compute_key across many invocations with varying pub_key values.
4. Use statistical timing analysis to recover bits of the private key, since the non-constant-time modular exponentiation will have data-dependent execution time.

Minimal trigger:
  DH *dh = DH_new();
  // Use a method without DH_FLAG_CACHE_MONT_P
  DH_generate_parameters_ex(dh, 2048, 2, NULL);
  DH_generate_key(dh);
  // dh->flags does NOT have DH_FLAG_CACHE_MONT_P
  // => dh->priv_key will NOT have BN_FLG_CONSTTIME
  // => bn_mod_exp will use variable-time algorithm
  DH_compute_key(key, pub_key, dh);

Fix: Move BN_set_flags(dh->priv_key, BN_FLG_CONSTTIME) outside the DH_FLAG_CACHE_MONT_P conditional, so it is always applied regardless of the flag state.
